# Next.js Architecture & Component Standards

## App Router Structure
Follow the established patterns in the website directory:
- [Main Layout](mdc:website/app/layout.tsx) — Root layout with metadata and global styles
- [Homepage](mdc:website/app/page.tsx) — Landing page
- [ZAG Matrix Page](mdc:website/app/zag-matrix/page.tsx) — Framework presentation
- [Newsletter Page](mdc:website/app/newsletter/page.tsx) — Email signup
- [Resources Page](mdc:website/app/resources/page.tsx) — Tools and frameworks
- [About Page](mdc:website/app/about/page.tsx) — Personal story
- [Contact Page](mdc:website/app/contact/page.tsx) — Contact form
- [Blog Pages](mdc:website/app/blog/) — Blog index and post routes

## Content pipeline (single source of truth)
- All blog posts live under repo root **`content/blog/`** (subdirs `zen/`, `act/`, `gem/`, `zag/`, etc.)
- Parsing and listing: [`website/lib/posts.ts`](mdc:website/lib/posts.ts) using `gray-matter` and Node `fs`
- **Do not** add a parallel content pipeline under `website/posts/` or use Contentlayer for blog posts
- Slug is derived from the **filename** (without extension); see [website/BLOG_SYSTEM_README.md](mdc:website/BLOG_SYSTEM_README.md)
- Images: `website/public/images/blog/<post-slug>/` referenced as `/images/blog/...` in markdown

## Component Architecture
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow the structure in [components directory](mdc:website/components/)
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS
- Use semantic HTML and accessibility best practices

